  "title": "Sorghum Roti: I. Traditional Methods of Consumption and Standard Procedures for Evaluation",
  "abstract": "Roti (an unleavened bread) is the most popular sorghum food consumed in India. The traditional methods of milling, dough and roti preparation are described in detail. Standard procedures for the dough and roti evaluation evolved at  ICRISAT are outlined.",
